    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** headlining the offense. With an elite efficiency score of 81.88, **Gunnar Henderson** occupies the prime leadoff spot against a favorable matchup and benefits from a significant 16% park factor boost. Critically, his profile today includes a \"Slow SP Delivery\" indicator, which provides a key 2% bump in SB probability\u2014the scarcest asset in our 5x5 build. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (70.49) and **Josh Jung** (62.36) also grade out as strong starts. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** leverages a 14% platoon advantage against a high-xERA starter, while **Josh Jung** utilizes a 10% park factor surge to comfortably clear the start threshold despite facing a respectable arm in Springs.\n\nWhile we are fielding a high-ceiling lineup, we must manage the risk presented by several tough opposing arms. **Luis Robert Jr.** (41.97) and **Andy Pages** (42.81) occupy the lower end of our starting efficiency range, largely suppressed by the elite nature of their respective matchups against Yamamoto and McLean. The most difficult personnel decision involved **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, who finished with a respectable 52.06 score. Although he carries a strong xwOBA, his score was dampened by a negative platoon and SP skill factors, leading us to favor the slightly higher-upside defensive and situational profiles of **Drake Baldwin** and **Jackson Merrill** today. We are playing a cautious hand with **Luis Robert Jr.**; his score is dragged down by a high-hold opposing pitcher that limits his high-end stolen base potential, serving as a reminder that even our elite speed threats must be deployed strategically to preserve game caps.",
